article.description: Freshman Seimone Augustus scored  six of her 27 points in overtime to lift fourth-ranked Louisiana State to a 78-71 victory over Arizona in the season opener for both teams.
article.headline: LSU has its hands full in season-opening win
article.linkText: Augustus dazzles in debut as No. 4 LSU holds off Arizona
article.story:
TUCSON, Az. (Ticker) -- Freshman Seimone Augustus scored  six of her 27 points in overtime to lift (No. 4 ESPN/USA Today, No. 3 AP) Louisiana State to a 78-71 victory over Arizona in the season opener for both teams.

Augustus, a consensus high school All-American, had a fabulous debut and one that LSU (1-0) needed. She made 12-of-17 shots, including a basket for a 71-69 lead with two minutes left in the extra session.

Augustus then found Doneeka Hodges for a layup and a four-point lead and added a pair of clutch free throws in the final minute. Her 27 points set a freshmen record for a Lady Tiger in her debut.

Aiysha Smith scored 15 points and Hodges added 12 for LSU, which blew a late lead by going scoreless over the final three minutes of regulation. Smith just missed on a desperation shot at the end of regulation that would have won it.

Freshman Shawntinice Pol collected 29 points and 11 rebounds for Arizona (0-1) and Krista Warren added 11 and 10. The Wildcats committed 22 turnovers, including seven by Aimee Grzyh.
